WEBVTT

00:02.460 --> 00:03.830
Previously on
"Marvel's Inhumans"...

00:03.830 --> 00:05.170
What is that?
That's my dog.
He needs a doctor.

00:05.170 --> 00:06.250
His name is Lockjaw.
Uh...
[ Chuckles nervously ]

00:06.250 --> 00:07.290
I'm a geneticist,

00:07.290 --> 00:08.330
but at my lab,
you'll be safe.

00:08.330 --> 00:09.830
You have a wife?
He's looking for her.

00:09.830 --> 00:11.080
I'll find her.

00:11.080 --> 00:12.290
Karnak:
Since I hit my head,

00:12.290 --> 00:15.170
I can't see the consequences
of my decisions.

00:15.170 --> 00:16.960
When my Terrigenesis
made me human,

00:16.960 --> 00:18.620
you abandoned me.

00:18.620 --> 00:19.750
I'm still your --
your friend.

00:19.750 --> 00:21.080
For how long this time?

00:22.540 --> 00:23.500
Mordis.

00:23.500 --> 00:25.830
[ Tires screeching ]

00:29.290 --> 00:31.830
Medusa: She can help us find
our family.

00:31.830 --> 00:33.290
I don't trust him.

00:33.290 --> 00:34.790
You didn't trust
me or Jen at first.

00:34.790 --> 00:35.540
Let me help you.

00:35.540 --> 00:38.120
♪♪

00:46.170 --> 00:54.170
♪♪

00:54.170 --> 01:02.460
♪♪

01:02.460 --> 01:04.500
Normally,
people I spend the night with

01:04.500 --> 01:07.290
leave before dawn's
first light.

01:07.290 --> 01:11.620
Just laying here with you,
I feel...

01:11.620 --> 01:14.750
Please say "good."

01:14.750 --> 01:17.710
No, I was -- I was
gonna say "phenomenal,"

01:17.710 --> 01:20.420
which is weird.

01:20.420 --> 01:24.290
It can't be post-conjugal
endorphins.

01:24.290 --> 01:26.880
We had intercourse
over five hours ago.

01:26.880 --> 01:29.290
"Intercourse"?
[ Chuckles ]

01:29.290 --> 01:34.000
I want to be around you,
like, all day.

01:34.000 --> 01:36.790
Thanks.

01:36.790 --> 01:39.540
This despite the fact
that you snore in your sleep.

01:39.540 --> 01:43.330
And the second toe
on your left foot is crooked.

01:43.330 --> 01:45.710
Should've stopped with,
"I want to be around you."

01:45.710 --> 01:47.330
[ Chuckles ]

01:47.330 --> 01:52.460
♪♪

01:52.460 --> 01:57.420
♪♪

01:57.420 --> 01:58.620
[ Bullets clink ]
[ Insect buzzing ]

01:58.620 --> 02:00.500
God!

02:00.500 --> 02:02.670
Hawaiian paradise, my ass.

02:02.670 --> 02:08.920
♪♪

02:08.920 --> 02:10.080
[ Breathes deeply ]

02:10.080 --> 02:12.040
[ Gun cocks ]

02:12.040 --> 02:15.960
♪♪

02:15.960 --> 02:18.500
Or m-maybe I'm just hungry.

02:18.500 --> 02:20.170
[ Chuckles ]

02:20.170 --> 02:22.670
Yeah, those, uh,
post-conjugal endorphins

02:22.670 --> 02:24.500
can really kick up
a hunger, huh?

02:24.500 --> 02:25.960
[ Chuckles ]

02:25.960 --> 02:30.790
♪♪

02:30.790 --> 02:32.710
Morning, Sunshines.

02:32.710 --> 02:42.000
♪♪

02:42.000 --> 02:51.290
♪♪

02:51.290 --> 02:53.750
Aah!

02:53.750 --> 02:55.620
Run.
Run!

02:55.620 --> 02:58.120
[ Gunshots ]

02:58.120 --> 03:04.460
♪♪

03:04.460 --> 03:05.710
How did you even --

03:05.710 --> 03:07.250
[ Gunshots ]

03:07.250 --> 03:12.120
♪♪

03:12.120 --> 03:13.540
Aah! Aah!

03:15.920 --> 03:18.540
Ted?

03:18.540 --> 03:20.670
Shh. Shh.
[ Muffled ] Oh, my God.

03:20.670 --> 03:24.120
Reno: Sharing was never
one of my strong points, Jen!

03:24.120 --> 03:26.330
Rough way to find out.
I know.

03:26.330 --> 03:28.500
But what are you gonna do?

03:28.500 --> 03:35.620
♪♪

03:35.620 --> 03:37.170
[ Rustling ]

03:40.580 --> 03:42.120
[ Breathing shallowly ]

03:42.120 --> 03:45.120
♪♪

03:45.120 --> 03:47.170
[ Cellphone rings ]

03:49.540 --> 03:51.040
Crap.

03:51.040 --> 03:53.790
[ Cellphone beeps ]

03:53.790 --> 03:55.420
Hey.

03:55.420 --> 03:57.170
You're on your way, huh?
You're early.

03:57.170 --> 03:58.710
I'll be waiting for you.

03:58.710 --> 04:00.710
[ Cellphone beeps ]

04:00.710 --> 04:04.790
♪♪

04:04.790 --> 04:07.080
We better move.

04:07.080 --> 04:09.290
[ Grunting ]

04:09.290 --> 04:12.000
[ Lo Tom's "Overboard" plays ]

04:12.000 --> 04:16.880
♪♪

04:20.290 --> 04:23.380
♪ You really messed me up ♪

04:23.380 --> 04:25.170
Yes, it hurt.

04:25.170 --> 04:28.170
♪ When you couldn't see me ♪

04:28.170 --> 04:30.460
We need to focus
on finding our family,

04:30.460 --> 04:32.170
on saving Crystal
from your brother.

04:36.210 --> 04:37.790
I don't want
to talk about it.

04:37.790 --> 04:41.250
It's not gonna change
anything.

04:41.250 --> 04:45.460
♪ Don't stop on account of me ♪

04:45.460 --> 04:48.830
♪ I'm not living there anymore ♪

04:48.830 --> 04:52.210
Pulsus.

04:52.210 --> 04:54.380
He shocked me.

04:54.380 --> 04:58.290
And Auran and some
of the other guards, they --

04:58.290 --> 05:03.380
they held me down, and --
and then he -- he --

05:03.380 --> 05:07.120
♪ It just takes a while ♪

05:07.120 --> 05:11.040
♪ For me to un-feel a thing ♪

05:11.960 --> 05:13.500
Hey.

05:13.500 --> 05:14.750
♪ And the opposite
of what you think ♪

05:14.750 --> 05:16.250
I'll be all right.

05:18.420 --> 05:20.250
Calm yourself.

05:20.250 --> 05:22.670
[ Pounding on trunk ]

05:22.670 --> 05:24.670
Okay. That's it. We are letting
that woman out of the trunk.

05:24.670 --> 05:30.620
♪♪

05:30.620 --> 05:36.330
♪♪

05:36.330 --> 05:38.790
Karnak's
over there somewhere.

05:38.790 --> 05:41.290
How do you know?

05:41.290 --> 05:44.500
[ Shrieks ]

05:44.500 --> 05:45.880
That's how I know.

05:45.880 --> 05:47.750
My call echo-locates
whatever I'm sent to find,

05:47.750 --> 05:49.330
even Royals.

05:49.330 --> 05:51.120
Well, I certainly
can't drive through that.

05:51.120 --> 05:52.880
Good,
'cause riding in that...

05:52.880 --> 05:53.960
What's that called?

05:53.960 --> 05:55.380
It's a trunk.

05:55.380 --> 05:56.960
And they're not meant
to be ridden in.

05:56.960 --> 05:58.290
Not that it's any different

05:58.290 --> 06:00.210
than how the Royal Family
normally treats us.

06:00.210 --> 06:02.290
♪♪

06:02.290 --> 06:04.710
Go.
Do your job.

06:04.710 --> 06:06.000
See?

06:09.580 --> 06:11.120
What?

06:11.120 --> 06:13.040
Do you really always
treat everybody that bad?

06:13.040 --> 06:15.790
Locus was here to kill us.

06:19.620 --> 06:21.040
This is good.

06:21.040 --> 06:24.000
We find Karnak
and then Gorgon,

06:24.000 --> 06:25.000
and then we return home

06:25.000 --> 06:26.380
and we make sure
that Crystal's safe.

06:29.250 --> 06:31.120
Karnak will find
a way home.

06:31.120 --> 06:33.790
Nobody knows this,
but my company's prepping

06:33.790 --> 06:36.830
a manned mission to the Moon
to beat the Chinese.

06:36.830 --> 06:38.620
I might be able to convince them
to let you guys tag along.

06:40.710 --> 06:42.080
They would find out
about our home.

06:42.080 --> 06:46.620
[ Comlink beeping ]

06:46.620 --> 06:47.790
Wait.
What is that?

06:47.790 --> 06:49.380
You hiding something
from us?

06:49.380 --> 06:51.040
[ Comlink beeps ]

06:51.040 --> 06:52.580
Locus.

06:53.960 --> 06:58.040
Why isn't Auran answering?

06:58.040 --> 06:59.250
Hello, Maximus.

06:59.250 --> 07:03.080
♪♪

07:03.080 --> 07:04.620
Medusa.

07:04.620 --> 07:07.500
Great.
You have Locus.

07:07.500 --> 07:09.330
You better not have hurt
my sister.

07:09.330 --> 07:11.170
Crystal is...

07:13.710 --> 07:15.500
I would never harm her.

07:15.500 --> 07:16.920
I don't want to hurt
any of you.

07:16.920 --> 07:18.920
Is that why you sent
Auran and her soldiers,

07:18.920 --> 07:20.210
why you released Mordis?

07:20.210 --> 07:22.040
Because we put him down,
too.

07:31.380 --> 07:34.210
Black Bolt says
that when he gets home,

07:34.210 --> 07:36.500
he wants to have
a few words with you.

07:36.500 --> 07:40.750
♪♪

07:40.750 --> 07:43.750
Tell my brother...

07:43.750 --> 07:45.920
I look forward
to the family reunion.

07:47.170 --> 07:48.170
[ Comlink cracks ]

07:48.170 --> 07:50.080
Ooh!
Can I see that?

07:52.960 --> 07:56.290
Bring me Tibor.
Now!

07:59.290 --> 08:05.380
♪♪

08:07.580 --> 08:12.080
[ Lockjaw panting ]

08:12.080 --> 08:14.580
Audrey:
Lockjaw's swelling is way down,
so we've got that going for us.

08:14.580 --> 08:15.830
Great.

08:15.830 --> 08:17.830
[ Lockjaw grunts ]

08:17.830 --> 08:19.620
We need to find
our family now.

08:19.620 --> 08:20.750
You ready?

08:20.750 --> 08:22.250
No, he's healing,

08:22.250 --> 08:24.290
but he's not ready
to be running around anywhere.

08:24.290 --> 08:26.250
That's okay.
We'll just transport.

08:26.250 --> 08:27.210
What do you mean,
"transport"?

08:27.210 --> 08:28.330
Just what I said.

08:28.330 --> 08:30.580
Lockjaw can transport
to any location

08:30.580 --> 08:32.120
and take people with him.

08:32.120 --> 08:33.620
Karnak calls it
"folding space."

08:33.620 --> 08:36.620
Does folding space make playing
fetch out of the question?

08:36.620 --> 08:38.620
No.
He loves that.

08:38.620 --> 08:40.960
Okay, I want to see.
This is ridiculous.

08:40.960 --> 08:42.380
How do you think
I got here from the Moon?

08:42.380 --> 08:43.460
I don't!

08:43.460 --> 08:45.330
We sent people
to the Moon.

08:45.330 --> 08:46.880
We took pictures
of the whole place.

08:46.880 --> 08:48.000
There's nothing there.

08:48.000 --> 08:49.380
Come on.
I want to try it.

08:49.380 --> 08:50.830
Don't play along with her.

08:50.830 --> 08:53.670
Come on, Dave.
Let's go.

08:53.670 --> 08:55.040
[ Lockjaw grunts ]

08:57.670 --> 08:59.790
Take us to where
you took Medusa.

08:59.790 --> 09:03.040
Get up close.
You have to be touching him.

09:03.040 --> 09:05.540
[ Lockjaw grunts ]

09:08.210 --> 09:12.290
♪♪

09:12.290 --> 09:13.540
Oh, my God.

09:13.540 --> 09:19.420
♪♪

09:20.960 --> 09:23.540
Declan:
That's fascinating.

09:23.540 --> 09:28.120
It's like a...
a serpent's venom gland...

09:28.120 --> 09:32.290
except in his neck,
not behind the eyes.

09:32.290 --> 09:37.920
♪♪

09:37.920 --> 09:43.500
♪♪

09:43.500 --> 09:44.790
[ Gasps ]

09:44.790 --> 09:47.380
[ Glove sizzling ]

09:47.380 --> 09:49.000
That's extraordinary.

09:50.960 --> 09:54.290
You think she has a power
of some kind, too?

09:54.290 --> 09:59.000
Set up a DNA test
on both of them.

09:59.000 --> 10:00.620
I have a feeling
they have a lot in common

10:00.620 --> 10:03.670
with our silent friend.

10:03.670 --> 10:08.040
♪♪

10:08.040 --> 10:12.000
[ Breathing heavily ]

10:12.000 --> 10:14.040
Where are you, Karnak?

10:20.960 --> 10:23.620
Karnak!
Karnak.

10:23.620 --> 10:27.540
Karnak.

10:27.540 --> 10:28.920
I've been looking
all over for you.

10:28.920 --> 10:30.460
Clearly, I didn't hide
well enough.

10:30.460 --> 10:32.040
Look what I found
out there.

10:33.420 --> 10:34.830
Huh?

10:34.830 --> 10:36.210
Want to play catch?

10:36.210 --> 10:38.250
Put that flag back
right now.

10:38.250 --> 10:40.250
No.
I found it out there.

10:40.250 --> 10:41.210
It's been out there
for years.

10:41.210 --> 10:43.710
Plus, it'll look great
in my room.

10:43.710 --> 10:46.790
You are putting
our civilization at risk.

10:46.790 --> 10:48.290
It's just a flag.

10:48.290 --> 10:49.710
A satellite's
gonna pass over

10:49.710 --> 10:52.290
where that flag was
in 22 minutes.

10:52.290 --> 10:54.960
So?

10:54.960 --> 10:59.210
Humans will wonder
what happened to the flag.

10:59.210 --> 11:03.580
They're gonna see your
hoofprints around where it was.

11:03.580 --> 11:05.460
Aren't they?

11:10.750 --> 11:12.330
21 minutes.

11:13.750 --> 11:15.620
Go!

11:15.620 --> 11:18.790
You would destroy Attilan
without me.

11:18.790 --> 11:21.040
Look good in his room.

11:21.040 --> 11:31.000
♪♪

11:31.000 --> 11:40.830
♪♪

11:40.830 --> 11:43.710
You got hurt.

11:43.710 --> 11:50.380
♪♪

11:50.380 --> 11:56.750
♪♪

11:56.750 --> 11:58.790
Don't worry.

11:58.790 --> 12:00.620
I'm coming for you.

12:00.620 --> 12:05.330
♪♪

12:05.330 --> 12:08.000
[ Sighs ]

12:08.000 --> 12:10.420
You scared me.

12:10.420 --> 12:12.040
Where are your partners?

12:14.920 --> 12:17.330
Ted had an accident.
Buried out back.

12:17.330 --> 12:20.290
However, I ran
into a little...glitch.

12:20.290 --> 12:22.960
Jen met some Asian dude
with face tatts.

12:22.960 --> 12:27.710
They took off after --
after they saw Ted's body.

12:27.710 --> 12:29.170
And now you're afraid
they'll go to the cops.

12:29.170 --> 12:31.500
I could use your help
finding them.

12:31.500 --> 12:33.380
You know,
the more, the merrier.

12:33.380 --> 12:36.710
What'd you do
with Ted's body?

12:36.710 --> 12:42.750
♪♪

12:42.750 --> 12:44.290
[ Sighs ]

12:44.290 --> 12:46.170
Whoa! Wait!

12:46.170 --> 12:47.580
[ Body thuds ]

12:47.580 --> 12:49.330
[ Birds squawking,
wings flapping ]

12:49.330 --> 12:52.920
I don't trust
people who kill their partners.

12:52.920 --> 12:54.670
You see that blood trail?

12:54.670 --> 12:58.170
You four, bring the truck in
as close as you can,

12:58.170 --> 12:59.670
load up the green.

12:59.670 --> 13:01.080
You, follow me.

13:01.080 --> 13:03.000
Let's make sure face-tatts
and his girlfriend

13:03.000 --> 13:04.880
don't make it out of here.

13:04.880 --> 13:09.120
♪♪

13:09.120 --> 13:13.380
♪♪

13:13.380 --> 13:15.330
Jen.

13:15.330 --> 13:16.460
Jen!

13:16.460 --> 13:22.920
♪♪

13:27.540 --> 13:30.500
♪♪

13:30.500 --> 13:33.750
♪♪

13:33.750 --> 13:35.880
You called for me,
my king?

13:35.880 --> 13:37.580
We're old friends.

13:37.580 --> 13:38.790
Enough of
the "my king" business.

13:38.790 --> 13:40.250
I have a task for you.

13:43.120 --> 13:44.920
Auran has failed
yet again.

13:44.920 --> 13:47.380
I need you to figure out

13:47.380 --> 13:49.040
which of these Inhumans
we could send to her.

13:49.040 --> 13:51.960
Like a forced
conscription?

13:51.960 --> 13:53.670
Call it whatever you want.

13:53.670 --> 13:56.420
The Royal Family can't
be allowed to return.

13:56.420 --> 13:58.620
If Black Bolt returns, they lose
their newfound freedom.

13:58.620 --> 14:01.330
I don't think
this is the freedom

14:01.330 --> 14:02.790
the lower caste
is looking for.

14:02.790 --> 14:05.420
That's the problem
with those people.

14:05.420 --> 14:07.330
They think that freedom
is something granted,

14:07.330 --> 14:10.420
but it's not freedom
until they earn it.

14:10.420 --> 14:12.830
Still, it's not
what they're expecting.

14:12.830 --> 14:15.170
Look, it's in
our best interest

14:15.170 --> 14:17.080
to have any confrontation
down there

14:17.080 --> 14:19.750
rather than have them come
back up here

14:19.750 --> 14:21.290
and ruin all we've done.

14:21.290 --> 14:22.960
I understand, Maximus.

14:25.500 --> 14:27.330
You know what?

14:27.330 --> 14:30.210
I've changed my mind.

14:30.210 --> 14:33.830
I like "my king" better.

14:33.830 --> 14:36.000
Yes, my king.

14:37.580 --> 14:47.670
♪♪

14:47.670 --> 14:49.830
[ Breathing heavily ]

14:49.830 --> 14:52.710
[ Groaning ]

14:57.580 --> 14:59.540
Ohh.
This hurts.

14:59.540 --> 15:00.790
Ohh.

15:00.790 --> 15:03.580
Complaining
will not do.

15:03.580 --> 15:06.750
Oh. Mm.
What are you doing?

15:06.750 --> 15:09.120
[ Bones crack ]
Mm!

15:09.120 --> 15:10.670
Huh.

15:10.670 --> 15:12.120
How did you do that?

15:12.120 --> 15:13.420
Blocked the pain nerves
in your side.

15:13.420 --> 15:15.540
You shouldn't feel
any pain there for a while.

15:15.540 --> 15:17.580
Show me the wound.

15:17.580 --> 15:19.040
[ Groans ]

15:21.000 --> 15:24.080
I should've seen this
before it happened to you.

15:24.080 --> 15:26.500
How would you have
done that?

15:26.500 --> 15:28.710
I'm usually good
at predicting outcomes.

15:28.710 --> 15:30.170
This is my fault.

15:30.170 --> 15:33.080
We need to get the bullet out
before we sew you up.

15:33.080 --> 15:34.920
Uh, uh, can't we just
leave it in there

15:34.920 --> 15:36.170
till we get to a hospital?

15:36.170 --> 15:38.540
Moving around
with the metal inside

15:38.540 --> 15:40.330
will cause internal damage,
and you'll die.

15:40.330 --> 15:43.380
Well, when you put it
like that...

15:43.380 --> 15:45.790
I could dig it out
from the front,

15:45.790 --> 15:47.880
but that would ensure
infection.

15:49.620 --> 15:52.540
Cut it out your back...

15:52.540 --> 15:55.250
but then we have to deal
with two open wounds.

15:57.620 --> 16:00.170
There is a path
to get it out.

16:00.170 --> 16:04.380
I need you to stay...
very still.

16:04.380 --> 16:06.170
What?
Why?

16:06.170 --> 16:08.080
Do you trust me?

16:10.790 --> 16:13.000
That's one of us.

16:14.750 --> 16:17.120
[ Groans softly ]

16:17.120 --> 16:18.420
What -- What are you doing?

16:18.420 --> 16:19.580
Stay still.

16:19.580 --> 16:21.250
You're like my cousin --
"Ooh! What's that?"

16:21.250 --> 16:23.830
Stay...still.

16:23.830 --> 16:29.040
♪♪

16:29.040 --> 16:30.960
[ Grunts ]

16:30.960 --> 16:32.920
[ Exhales sharply ]

16:32.920 --> 16:34.170
Wait.
Is that...?

16:34.170 --> 16:35.830
[ Groans ]

16:35.830 --> 16:38.830
[ Exhales sharply ]

16:38.830 --> 16:40.170
How did you...?

16:40.170 --> 16:41.250
One of the rare times

16:41.250 --> 16:43.210
the shortest distance
between two points

16:43.210 --> 16:44.960
is actually
a straight line.

16:44.960 --> 16:51.500
♪♪

16:51.500 --> 16:57.830
♪♪

16:57.830 --> 17:01.170
[ Sighs ]

17:01.170 --> 17:02.960
Mm.

17:02.960 --> 17:05.080
[ Breathing heavily ]

17:07.290 --> 17:08.960
What are you doing
with that?

17:08.960 --> 17:11.880
Improvising a suture
to sew you up.

17:11.880 --> 17:13.710
Uh, no.

17:13.710 --> 17:16.830
Just no.

17:16.830 --> 17:18.170
I've got a sewing kit.

17:20.120 --> 17:22.460
We're always tearing holes
in our tents.

17:22.460 --> 17:25.960
[ Sighs ]

17:25.960 --> 17:27.920
[ Birds chirping ]

17:27.920 --> 17:29.750
[ Exhales forcefully ]

17:29.750 --> 17:32.790
Once you get me closed up,
we have to call the police.

17:32.790 --> 17:34.250
No.

17:34.250 --> 17:36.620
Your kind tends to react badly
to anyone different,

17:36.620 --> 17:39.620
especially those
in authority.

17:39.620 --> 17:42.670
And trudging through
the jungle to the police

17:42.670 --> 17:44.830
won't stop Reno
from hunting us.

17:44.830 --> 17:46.790
We can't stay here.

17:46.790 --> 17:48.710
No.

17:52.080 --> 17:53.790
But we can go back to camp.

17:53.790 --> 17:56.040
Wait.
Go back?

17:56.040 --> 17:58.120
What?
Like, to ambush him?

17:58.120 --> 18:01.000
I don't see
a flaw in the plan.

18:03.460 --> 18:06.210
I don't think I see the flaw
in anything in my current state.

18:06.210 --> 18:08.620
[ Branches cracking,
leaves rustling ]

18:08.620 --> 18:10.620
[ Grunts ]

18:10.620 --> 18:14.080
♪♪

18:16.080 --> 18:19.670
So...

18:19.670 --> 18:21.960
both of them seem to have
DNA similar to the silent one.

18:21.960 --> 18:23.290
Mm-hmm.

18:23.290 --> 18:25.750
Except there seems to be
a slight degradation

18:25.750 --> 18:27.330
in the female's DNA.

18:27.330 --> 18:29.880
All these people
with powers...

18:29.880 --> 18:32.460
What if they stopped
fighting each other
and turned against us?

18:32.460 --> 18:35.040
Well, all the more reason
why we have to help them

18:35.040 --> 18:36.380
and understand them.

18:36.380 --> 18:38.670
[ Tray clatters ]

18:38.670 --> 18:43.210
♪♪

18:43.210 --> 18:47.750
♪♪

18:47.750 --> 18:50.670
Relax.
It's just a postmortem spasm.

18:50.670 --> 18:53.170
♪♪

18:53.170 --> 18:54.750
[ Gasps ]

18:54.750 --> 19:03.380
♪♪

19:03.380 --> 19:11.710
♪♪

19:11.710 --> 19:20.210
♪♪

19:20.210 --> 19:22.830
[ Choking ]

19:22.830 --> 19:24.960
Please stop.
Ow!

19:24.960 --> 19:27.210
Tell me where Black Bolt is,
or I'll snap your neck.

19:27.210 --> 19:29.330
What's a Black Bolt?

19:29.330 --> 19:31.420
The one who doesn't speak.

19:31.420 --> 19:33.540
I was helping him.
[ Gasps ]

19:33.540 --> 19:36.040
You were helping
Black Bolt?

19:36.040 --> 19:38.040
I helped him...
get away from jail.

19:38.040 --> 19:40.250
Why would he even care
about you?

19:40.250 --> 19:42.080
I was helping him find
his wife.

19:42.080 --> 19:43.880
[ Gasps ]

19:45.580 --> 19:48.330
Who are you,
and what did you do to Sakas?

19:48.330 --> 19:50.040
He was killed
in the explosion.

19:50.040 --> 19:52.830
I was -- I was performing
an autopsy on him.

19:52.830 --> 19:55.170
You were dead --
both of you were.

19:55.170 --> 19:56.750
Wait.

19:56.750 --> 19:57.790
Black Bolt owes you?

19:57.790 --> 19:59.710
In a way, yes.

19:59.710 --> 20:03.330
♪♪

20:03.330 --> 20:04.960
Aah!

20:04.960 --> 20:10.080
♪♪

20:16.790 --> 20:18.580
Looks like nobody's there.

20:18.580 --> 20:20.460
I don't know.

20:20.460 --> 20:21.830
What?

20:21.830 --> 20:23.170
I-I can't see my way

20:23.170 --> 20:24.960
to a clear, definite ending
for this plan.

20:24.960 --> 20:27.290
Yeah.
So?

20:27.290 --> 20:29.250
How -- How do I act
on a plan

20:29.250 --> 20:31.330
when I feel
this doubt?

20:31.330 --> 20:33.790
You just make
the best decision you can.

20:33.790 --> 20:35.500
Everybody has doubt.

20:35.500 --> 20:39.420
I don't doubt
anything that I do.

20:39.420 --> 20:43.040
At least I didn't
before I hurt my head.

20:43.040 --> 20:45.790
You know that people
who don't feel doubt

20:45.790 --> 20:49.040
are the scariest people
on this planet, right?

20:49.040 --> 20:51.580
Why?

20:51.580 --> 20:55.250
Because doubt
is our friend.

20:55.250 --> 20:59.620
It makes us question things,
helps us find new solutions.

20:59.620 --> 21:02.460
Only crazy fanatics
don't feel doubt.

21:02.460 --> 21:05.540
You -- You would have m--
have me just --

21:05.540 --> 21:08.500
just go, like --
like my cousin Gorgon?

21:08.500 --> 21:10.540
Yeah.

21:10.540 --> 21:16.500
But Gorgon is right
62 percent of the time,

21:16.500 --> 21:18.830
which means
there's 38 percent of the time

21:18.830 --> 21:22.250
where I have to step in
and make things right.

21:22.250 --> 21:24.790
Well,
I've got your back.

21:24.790 --> 21:28.420
That's got to be good
for at least 14 percent of help

21:28.420 --> 21:30.790
when things go bad.

21:32.580 --> 21:34.460
Come on.

21:34.460 --> 21:37.330
I believe in you.

21:38.710 --> 21:41.040
I put everything back.

21:41.040 --> 21:43.750
And I even cleaned up
my hoofprints.

21:43.750 --> 21:45.880
Just barely in time, too.

21:45.880 --> 21:48.040
The whole time, I was thinking,
"How would Karnak handle this?"

21:48.040 --> 21:50.040
You could never handle
anything like I do.

21:50.040 --> 21:52.040
That would be almost
as impossible

21:52.040 --> 21:54.540
as me handling anything
as moronically as you.

21:54.540 --> 21:56.290
Yeah, well,
now you're just being mean.

21:56.290 --> 21:58.880
I'm just stating a truth.

21:58.880 --> 22:00.620
Thanks to Terrigenesis,

22:00.620 --> 22:03.000
you will always be the one
making a mess of things.

22:03.000 --> 22:06.750
I will always be the one
cleaning them up.

22:06.750 --> 22:08.880
But at least I'll have
some fun along the way.

22:08.880 --> 22:10.040
And look at you.

22:10.040 --> 22:11.830
Even when you play games,

22:11.830 --> 22:13.290
you're still stuck
doing nothing.

22:25.460 --> 22:28.380
14 percent sounds
like the right number.

22:28.380 --> 22:31.040
Let's go.

22:33.500 --> 22:36.380
[ Grunts, inhales sharply ]

22:36.380 --> 22:38.420
Under no circumstances
will you allow

22:38.420 --> 22:41.000
any harm to come to my ally,
Dr. Declan.

22:41.000 --> 22:42.290
Wait. What?

22:42.290 --> 22:44.040
And don't tell him
you're with me.

22:44.040 --> 22:45.790
He wouldn't understand
why I sent you.

22:45.790 --> 22:47.500
Wait. Wait.
He had Black Bolt.

22:47.500 --> 22:49.330
Why didn't
you have him killed?

22:49.330 --> 22:51.380
That's not for you
to question.

22:51.380 --> 22:53.540
Declan is important
because of his research

22:53.540 --> 22:55.710
on the humans who have
undergone Terrigenesis.

22:55.710 --> 22:58.290
I don't like the idea
of consorting with this human.

22:58.290 --> 22:59.790
I don't understand.

22:59.790 --> 23:01.880
You don't need to.

23:01.880 --> 23:04.000
Just...keep him safe,

23:04.000 --> 23:05.960
find Black Bolt and the rest
of the Royal Family,

23:05.960 --> 23:08.210
and finish your mission.

23:08.210 --> 23:09.750
I'll be sending you
some help soon.

23:09.750 --> 23:11.040
Who?

23:11.040 --> 23:15.210
Whatever happened
to, "Yes, my king"?

23:15.210 --> 23:18.080
Yes, my king.

23:18.080 --> 23:26.500
♪♪

23:26.500 --> 23:34.620
♪♪

23:34.620 --> 23:37.460
[ Vines sizzle ]

23:39.420 --> 23:41.580
Aah!

23:41.580 --> 23:43.750
Really?

23:43.750 --> 23:46.670
Well, get him.

23:46.670 --> 23:52.290
♪♪

23:52.290 --> 23:54.580
[ Vine cracks ]
Ohh!

23:56.540 --> 23:58.920
[ Grunting ]

23:58.920 --> 24:01.120
Well, look at you
with the hot hands.

24:02.170 --> 24:03.750
Think he's one of us?

24:03.750 --> 24:05.420
[ Comlink beeps ]

24:05.420 --> 24:07.290
Auran: Where are you?

24:07.290 --> 24:11.000
Well, we stayed on the trail
of Black Bolt, but we lost him.

24:11.000 --> 24:13.710
Did manage to capture
the other human, though.

24:13.710 --> 24:14.960
Hey, you know he's got
abilities?

24:14.960 --> 24:16.080
I didn't.

24:16.080 --> 24:17.500
Yeah.

24:17.500 --> 24:20.000
He says that
he and Black Bolt are friends.

24:20.000 --> 24:21.750
He helped him escape
from jail.

24:21.750 --> 24:24.250
Bring him back to me.

24:24.250 --> 24:26.080
We need him.

24:29.420 --> 24:31.040
[ Birds chirping ]

24:31.040 --> 24:32.670
No sign of Reno.

24:32.670 --> 24:35.040
See?
You were right.

24:42.000 --> 24:45.580
What are the odds of these
versus Reno's gun?

24:45.580 --> 24:47.580
I'd go with the gun.

24:47.580 --> 24:49.710
[ Sighs ]

24:52.620 --> 25:02.000
♪♪

25:02.000 --> 25:11.540
♪♪

25:11.540 --> 25:21.120
♪♪

25:21.120 --> 25:22.790
You got some reach
with that one.

25:22.790 --> 25:26.670
♪♪

25:26.670 --> 25:30.790
♪♪

25:30.790 --> 25:32.960
These weren't there
when we left.

25:32.960 --> 25:35.210
Someone else has been here.

25:35.210 --> 25:38.210
[ Vehicle approaching ]

25:41.170 --> 25:43.620
Get in there.

25:43.620 --> 25:46.540
[ Grunts ]

25:46.540 --> 25:52.120
♪♪

25:52.120 --> 25:54.170
[ Brakes squeal ]

25:57.580 --> 25:59.750
Load it up!

25:59.750 --> 26:07.750
♪♪

26:14.000 --> 26:17.880
-Got room for it?
-Yeah.

26:17.880 --> 26:19.040
They're robbing us?

26:19.040 --> 26:21.380
Seems unlikely.

26:21.380 --> 26:23.000
They came prepared.

26:23.000 --> 26:25.710
Reno cut a deal
on the side.

26:25.710 --> 26:27.080
That makes sense.

26:27.080 --> 26:29.000
Sneak out the back.
Hide.

26:29.000 --> 26:30.460
Why?

26:30.460 --> 26:32.540
I need you somewhere safe
while I take them down.

26:32.540 --> 26:35.540
If Reno's in league with them,
four is better than five.

26:35.540 --> 26:37.170
I don't doubt that math.

26:39.580 --> 26:41.120
Be careful.

26:41.120 --> 26:43.420
[ Grunts ]

26:43.420 --> 26:49.750
♪♪

26:49.750 --> 26:55.790
♪♪

26:55.790 --> 26:58.000
Whoo!
Good boy.

26:58.000 --> 27:00.920
Dave:
This is incredible!

27:05.580 --> 27:07.620
Wow!

27:07.620 --> 27:11.380
Kind of gives you a jolt
in your fillings, you know?

27:11.380 --> 27:14.460
Oh, Crystal,
we've been all over the island

27:14.460 --> 27:15.620
in the blink of an eye.

27:15.620 --> 27:18.540
Do you know how long
that would take us to drive?

27:19.830 --> 27:21.420
My family
could be anywhere.

27:21.420 --> 27:23.330
This place is enormous.

27:23.330 --> 27:26.000
Want to know
the state quote of Hawaii?

27:27.210 --> 27:30.540
"This is my office!"

27:30.540 --> 27:31.710
[ Laughs ]

27:31.710 --> 27:33.420
I don't get it.

27:33.420 --> 27:34.540
Ah, it's okay.

27:34.540 --> 27:37.000
It's kind of a dumb thing
to say, anyway.

27:37.000 --> 27:39.080
[ Grunts ]

27:43.420 --> 27:47.210
I can control the elements,
but this...

27:47.210 --> 27:49.250
There is so much water.

27:49.250 --> 27:50.540
It looks like
it keeps coming toward us.

27:50.540 --> 27:52.620
It's --
It's the tides.

27:52.620 --> 27:55.420
They say it actually
affects normal people.

27:55.420 --> 27:56.500
But you?

27:56.500 --> 27:58.750
It's overwhelming.

27:58.750 --> 28:02.500
I bet they don't have
anything like this on the Moon.

28:02.500 --> 28:03.710
No.

28:03.710 --> 28:05.960
Everything is very controlled
in Attilan.

28:05.960 --> 28:07.290
I always feel separate

28:07.290 --> 28:08.830
from everyone
outside the Royal Family.

28:08.830 --> 28:11.330
You don't get to hang out
with any friends?

28:11.330 --> 28:15.120
It's just me and Lockjaw
mostly.

28:15.120 --> 28:17.120
Well, even if I did
have friends to,

28:17.120 --> 28:20.380
what did you call it,
"hang out with,"

28:20.380 --> 28:22.710
my sister, Medusa,
is so protective.

28:22.710 --> 28:26.750
Things are pretty lax
here in Hawaii.

28:26.750 --> 28:29.710
Our other state motto
is, "Hang loose."

28:31.540 --> 28:32.920
Hang loose?

28:32.920 --> 28:35.620
Don't let life
wind you up tight, you know?

28:35.620 --> 28:37.750
Like, if you feel like,
I don't know, uh,

28:37.750 --> 28:40.790
doing a handstand,
you do it!

28:40.790 --> 28:42.080
[ Laughing ]

28:42.080 --> 28:45.210
You're different
than I expected.

28:45.210 --> 28:47.710
I never expected
being with a human would be...

28:47.710 --> 28:49.080
What? Fun?

28:49.080 --> 28:50.620
...safe.

28:52.960 --> 28:54.210
All we ever saw of humanity

28:54.210 --> 28:57.460
was war and terrorism --
awful things.

28:57.460 --> 29:00.170
Yeah, there -- there are
bad people out there.

29:00.170 --> 29:03.540
But I'm safe,
and most humans are.

29:03.540 --> 29:07.580
You can't live life
all afraid, you know?

29:07.580 --> 29:09.750
You -- Sometimes, you just --
you just got to go for it.

29:09.750 --> 29:13.040
Like...do you want to run
out into the ocean?

29:13.040 --> 29:15.620
You do it!

29:15.620 --> 29:21.670
♪♪

29:21.670 --> 29:23.330
You have fun!

29:23.330 --> 29:25.210
Come on!

29:26.880 --> 29:28.540
My family.

29:28.540 --> 29:31.250
We'll find
your family later!

29:31.250 --> 29:34.120
But right now,
hang loose!

29:34.120 --> 29:37.120
Come on!

29:37.120 --> 29:46.330
♪♪

29:46.330 --> 29:48.120
[ Insects chirping ]

29:55.330 --> 29:58.120
[ Indistinct chatter ]

30:00.790 --> 30:03.080
[ Locus shrieks ]

30:03.080 --> 30:05.250
-Hey, it's that guy!
-Get him!

30:05.250 --> 30:12.880
♪♪

30:12.880 --> 30:20.540
♪♪

30:20.540 --> 30:28.460
♪♪

30:28.460 --> 30:36.040
♪♪

30:36.040 --> 30:37.830
Aah!

30:41.540 --> 30:43.540
[ Groans ]

30:43.540 --> 30:47.380
♪♪

30:47.380 --> 30:49.380
Hey!

30:49.380 --> 30:51.170
Let him go,
or I'll burn all this!

30:51.170 --> 30:52.420
Don't do nothing stupid!

30:52.420 --> 30:54.670
Do it!

30:54.670 --> 30:59.330
♪♪

30:59.330 --> 31:00.830
They care more for the crop
than us.

31:00.830 --> 31:08.540
♪♪

31:13.500 --> 31:16.120
[ Shrieks ]

31:16.120 --> 31:19.120
[ Shrieks ]

31:19.120 --> 31:21.500
We're close.

31:21.500 --> 31:24.170
H-H-How exactly
does that thing work?

31:24.170 --> 31:25.500
I don't know.
It just does.

31:25.500 --> 31:27.580
So you feel
this Karnak guy's what --

31:27.580 --> 31:30.790
his, um -- his location,
his distance from you?

31:30.790 --> 31:32.420
Yes to all of that.

31:32.420 --> 31:35.330
And that makes you, what?
The Royal finder of things?

31:35.330 --> 31:37.380
Medusa:
Terrigenesis decides all.

31:37.380 --> 31:39.250
Well, I don't think
I'd like that.

31:39.250 --> 31:41.000
Try being me.

31:41.000 --> 31:43.330
If something goes missing,
I have to find it.

31:43.330 --> 31:45.120
But think of all the good
that you're doing.

31:45.120 --> 31:47.460
Pre-Terrigenesis,
I wanted to be a healer.

31:47.460 --> 31:49.210
She can't do both?

31:49.210 --> 31:52.420
Finding is Locus'
one true path in our society.

31:52.420 --> 31:54.290
And you wonder
why I chose Maximus.

31:54.290 --> 31:55.620
Do you dare speak
against our king?

31:55.620 --> 31:57.500
Your parents dared.

31:57.500 --> 31:58.750
And his parents
banished them for it.

31:58.750 --> 32:00.250
Wait. What?

32:00.250 --> 32:01.420
You married the son

32:01.420 --> 32:02.580
of the people who banished
your parents?

32:02.580 --> 32:03.670
It's not like it sounds.

32:03.670 --> 32:05.170
[ Fingers snap ]

32:07.080 --> 32:09.290
We were alone.

32:09.290 --> 32:11.040
His parents died
shortly after mine did.

32:12.790 --> 32:14.670
We understood loss.

32:14.670 --> 32:16.620
It connected us.

32:16.620 --> 32:18.670
I hear you,
but isn't it ironic

32:18.670 --> 32:19.960
that you guys
have been thrown out

32:19.960 --> 32:21.880
for not wanting to change
the caste system

32:21.880 --> 32:23.210
while your parents did?

32:23.210 --> 32:27.080
The laws of the land in Attilan
aren't perfect,

32:27.080 --> 32:29.580
but we're always working towards
the good of Inhumanity.

32:29.580 --> 32:31.120
You make it sound
like there's no choice

32:31.120 --> 32:33.170
in how you oversee
the law.

32:33.170 --> 32:36.620
Maximus cares enough about us
to want to change things.

32:36.620 --> 32:38.000
We've made mistakes,

32:38.000 --> 32:40.290
and we know the system
isn't perfect for everyone,

32:40.290 --> 32:41.830
but we always try
to do what's best.

32:41.830 --> 32:44.120
Wasn't it Maximus
who forced you to come here

32:44.120 --> 32:46.210
and use your gift to find us?

32:46.210 --> 32:53.580
♪♪

32:58.540 --> 33:02.420
They don't understand because
you've been guarded for so long.

33:05.120 --> 33:08.000
Maybe it's time
everyone knows you like I do.

33:08.000 --> 33:15.040
♪♪

33:15.040 --> 33:22.330
♪♪

33:22.330 --> 33:24.880
I have the full list
of lower-caste abilities.

33:28.920 --> 33:30.790
Some promising ones here.

33:30.790 --> 33:32.380
Maximus: Good.

33:36.830 --> 33:38.790
Isn't this
Bronaja's father?

33:38.790 --> 33:41.750
He's a level eight
in strength.

33:41.750 --> 33:45.540
He was also the only one
who considered it an honor

33:45.540 --> 33:48.000
to be drafted
into your mission.

33:48.000 --> 33:50.750
The others
were not as happy.

33:59.460 --> 34:03.120
You have to earn
your freedom.

34:03.120 --> 34:06.290
Look at me.

34:06.290 --> 34:08.790
I sacrificed everything
for Attilan.

34:11.540 --> 34:15.540
Do you really think I wanted
to lose my family?

34:15.540 --> 34:18.120
To send Auran to kill
my own flesh and blood?

34:18.120 --> 34:22.380
Forgive me,
but some Inhumans might wonder

34:22.380 --> 34:25.170
if this is for the good
of Attilan...

34:25.170 --> 34:26.420
or for the good
of Maximus.

34:26.420 --> 34:28.080
What?

34:28.080 --> 34:33.500
♪♪

34:33.500 --> 34:36.080
How dare you suggest
that this was all for me.

34:36.080 --> 34:39.170
I'm speaking to you
as a friend.

34:39.170 --> 34:43.250
I don't need friends who
constantly tear down my plans.

34:43.250 --> 34:45.290
Go.

34:48.670 --> 34:52.000
Yes, my king.

34:52.000 --> 34:58.920
♪♪

34:58.920 --> 35:05.880
♪♪

35:05.880 --> 35:13.080
♪♪

35:13.080 --> 35:18.460
Father, you don't understand.

35:18.460 --> 35:23.210
You weren't there as everyone
looked at me in pity.

35:23.210 --> 35:26.080
If I'd gotten an ability,
anything but being human,

35:26.080 --> 35:29.170
I could have been king!

35:29.170 --> 35:32.670
None of this
would have happened.

35:32.670 --> 35:36.330
But now I've lost my brother,
my cousin,

35:36.330 --> 35:39.170
all for the greater good
of Attilan!

35:42.830 --> 35:49.920
♪♪

35:49.920 --> 35:52.670
[ Breathing heavily ]

35:52.670 --> 35:56.380
♪♪

35:56.380 --> 35:58.540
[ Grunts ]

35:58.540 --> 36:00.710
Wait.

36:00.710 --> 36:02.710
How would Karnak handle this?

36:06.540 --> 36:14.750
♪♪

36:14.750 --> 36:16.500
Where's Jen?

36:16.500 --> 36:18.540
Getting a preview
of what's gonna happen to her

36:18.540 --> 36:20.210
if you don't tell me
who you're working with

36:20.210 --> 36:22.210
or why you burned
my crops.

36:22.210 --> 36:25.330
I'll tell you everything,
but you're not gonna believe me.

36:25.330 --> 36:26.750
Try me.

36:29.040 --> 36:32.250
I'm Karnak.

36:32.250 --> 36:36.250
I'm from a city on the Moon,
and I'm an Inhuman.

36:38.830 --> 36:40.080
Stick to the body for now.

36:42.460 --> 36:45.960
[ Grunting ]

36:45.960 --> 36:48.330
[ Blows landing ]

36:52.080 --> 36:53.670
Hyah!

36:53.670 --> 36:55.880
[ Rumbling ]

36:59.790 --> 37:02.790
[ Grunts ]

37:02.790 --> 37:11.670
♪♪

37:11.670 --> 37:13.500
Free yourself.

37:13.500 --> 37:15.040
I can't.

37:15.040 --> 37:17.960
[ Exhales forcefully ]

37:17.960 --> 37:19.080
Get the girl.
Who?

37:19.080 --> 37:20.710
-The girl!
-Oh.

37:22.750 --> 37:23.750
Who are you?

37:23.750 --> 37:25.170
Gorgon.

37:25.170 --> 37:26.830
He talks about you
a lot.

37:26.830 --> 37:27.670
Wait.
Really?

37:27.670 --> 37:30.210
Uh-huh.

37:33.080 --> 37:34.750
Before you tell me

37:34.750 --> 37:36.620
how stupid I was
to stomp my way in here --
Stop!

37:36.620 --> 37:37.620
Thank you.

37:39.040 --> 37:41.750
We got to go!

37:41.750 --> 37:46.790
♪♪

37:46.790 --> 37:49.790
[ Insects chirping ]

37:55.960 --> 37:57.790
I like your new clothes.

37:57.790 --> 37:59.880
Another word,
and I kill you.

37:59.880 --> 38:02.000
Sorry we lost Black Bolt.

38:02.000 --> 38:03.830
The days of chasing
Black Bolt are over.

38:03.830 --> 38:04.620
Oh.
We're going back home?

38:04.620 --> 38:06.040
No.

38:06.040 --> 38:08.420
We'll complete the mission
King Maximus gave us.

38:08.420 --> 38:10.210
We'll hold
these pitiful humans hostage

38:10.210 --> 38:12.540
and force Black Bolt
to come to us.

38:12.540 --> 38:14.790
[ Coughs ]

38:14.790 --> 38:16.250
Ohh.

38:16.250 --> 38:17.830
I don't think
that I can keep this up.

38:17.830 --> 38:19.580
I never liked retreating,
anyway.

38:19.580 --> 38:21.830
It's good to have you
by my side.

38:21.830 --> 38:23.830
Seriously.
Are you okay?

38:25.420 --> 38:28.000
I'm not sure,
but I mean what I say.

38:28.000 --> 38:30.580
[ Gunshots, men screaming ]

38:34.920 --> 38:36.670
[ Gunshots, screaming continue ]

38:36.670 --> 38:42.540
♪♪

38:42.540 --> 38:48.170
♪♪

38:48.170 --> 38:50.170
Black Bolt!
[ Laughs ]

38:51.710 --> 38:55.380
Medusa, you okay?
We heard gunshots.

38:55.380 --> 38:57.960
Yeah,
we took care of them.

38:59.330 --> 39:00.620
What happened to your hair?

39:00.620 --> 39:02.120
It's a long story.

39:04.710 --> 39:06.580
You're a welcome sight, too,
my king.

39:06.580 --> 39:14.170
♪♪

39:14.170 --> 39:17.040
Who's this lovely human?

39:17.040 --> 39:18.380
I'm Louise.

39:18.380 --> 39:20.500
Sorry to break up
this Moon-people reunion,

39:20.500 --> 39:22.420
but I need to find a phone
and call the police.

39:22.420 --> 39:23.920
All of you should leave.

39:23.920 --> 39:25.120
The police?
You'll get in trouble.

39:25.120 --> 39:26.120
Leave with us.

39:26.120 --> 39:28.580
I'll make an anonymous call,

39:28.580 --> 39:30.960
but you don't want to be hassled
by the cops.

39:30.960 --> 39:33.670
You're like the epitome
of illegal aliens.

39:33.670 --> 39:35.250
We thank you.

39:36.880 --> 39:38.290
One moment.

39:38.290 --> 39:40.250
[ Groans ]

39:40.250 --> 39:43.460
♪♪

39:43.460 --> 39:46.960
You're sending me off
before dawn's first light.

39:46.960 --> 39:48.580
It's not like that.

39:48.580 --> 39:50.170
We had a good time,

39:50.170 --> 39:52.290
but now we have to go
our own ways.

39:52.290 --> 39:54.880
Sometimes,
life is just like that.

39:54.880 --> 40:00.750
♪♪

40:00.750 --> 40:03.170
Don't be so hard
on yourself.

40:03.170 --> 40:05.420
A little doubt
is good for you.

40:05.420 --> 40:10.620
♪♪

40:10.620 --> 40:15.880
♪♪

40:15.880 --> 40:20.250
One day, 6 hours, 46 minutes.

40:20.250 --> 40:28.290
♪♪

40:28.290 --> 40:30.670
Look at you.

40:30.670 --> 40:34.830
Good for you.

40:34.830 --> 40:36.460
Louise: Oh, my God.

40:37.790 --> 40:39.460
Medusa:
She's been shot.

40:39.460 --> 40:42.080
[ Locus groans softly ]

40:44.170 --> 40:46.540
This is a fatal wound.

40:46.540 --> 40:51.000
Remember, you can change.

40:51.000 --> 40:53.920
Please...

40:53.920 --> 40:56.420
be the king we deserve.

40:56.420 --> 41:00.040
♪♪

41:00.040 --> 41:02.670
Good.

41:02.670 --> 41:04.710
Crystal's here.

41:04.710 --> 41:06.790
What?

41:06.790 --> 41:08.380
On the island.

41:08.380 --> 41:10.040
Where?

41:10.040 --> 41:11.380
Where is she?

41:11.380 --> 41:13.540
Please.
Where is she?

41:16.500 --> 41:20.210
♪♪

41:28.000 --> 41:33.330
♪♪

41:33.330 --> 41:38.500
♪♪

41:42.460 --> 41:44.830
No.
Please.

41:44.830 --> 41:46.710
Tell King Maximus I'm loyal.

41:46.710 --> 41:48.960
What were you and the king
talking about, Tibor?

41:48.960 --> 41:50.960
I'm sorry.

41:53.210 --> 41:55.540
I won't speak out against
any of his plans ever again.

41:55.540 --> 41:57.540
Please.

41:57.540 --> 41:59.330
You defied Maximus?

41:59.330 --> 42:00.670
No, not defied.
No.

42:00.670 --> 42:02.080
I only pointed out

42:02.080 --> 42:06.250
how some of his people
might feel about his rule.

42:08.710 --> 42:11.580
We are some
of those people.

42:11.580 --> 42:13.420
We need your assistance

42:13.420 --> 42:16.500
to take down
the false king of Attilan.

42:16.500 --> 42:20.330
♪♪

42:25.000 --> 42:34.580
♪♪

42:34.580 --> 42:43.960
♪♪

42:43.960 --> 42:53.380
♪♪
